        <div class="tc-breadcrumb"><a href="/landing">Rhythm Library System</a> › Three Camps Drum Exercise</div>
        <h1>Three Camps Drum Exercise</h1>
        <p class="tc-hero-sub">Build Control, Flow, and Drumset Vocabulary</p>
        <p class="tc-hero-desc">Three Camps is one of the most effective drum exercises for developing hand control, rhythmic reading, and musical vocabulary — used in the Rhythm Library System to generate hundreds of sticking pattern combinations.</p>
        <button class="tc-btn-primary" @onclick='() => Nav.NavigateTo("/")'>Launch Three Camps in the Free App →</button>
    </section>

    <!-- What Is It -->
    <div class="tc-white">
        <div class="tc-section">
            <div class="tc-label">What Is Three Camps?</div>
            <h2>A classic rudimental exercise reimagined as a practice system</h2>
            <p>Three Camps is a traditional rudimental snare drum exercise that has been used in drum education for generations. In its classic form it is a short, repeating phrase built from a combination of single strokes, double strokes, and rolls arranged in a specific rhythmic pattern.</p>
            <p>In the <strong>Rhythm Library System</strong>, Three Camps takes on a new role. Rather than simply repeating the exercise as written, it becomes a <strong>rhythmic framework</strong> — a sequence of note values that you apply different sticking patterns to. Each time you change the sticking pattern, you hear a completely different musical phrase built from the same underlying rhythm.</p>
            <p>This transforms a single exercise into a practice tool that can keep a drummer busy for years.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Why It Matters -->
    <div class="tc-gray">
        <div class="tc-section">
            <div class="tc-label">Why It Matters</div>
            <h2>What Three Camps helps you develop</h2>
            <div class="tc-benefits-grid">
                <div class="tc-benefit-card">
                    <div class="tc-benefit-icon">🎼</div>
                    <h3>Rhythmic Reading</h3>
                    <p>Following the notation in real time builds the connection between what you see on the page and what you play on the kit.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="tc-benefit-card">
                    <div class="tc-benefit-icon">🥁</div>
                    <h3>Hand Control</h3>
                    <p>Applying different sticking patterns to the same rhythm forces both hands to work through unfamiliar sequences at a controlled tempo.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="tc-benefit-card">
                    <div class="tc-benefit-icon">🎯</div>
                    <h3>Right- and Left-Hand Lead</h3>
                    <p>Practicing both right-hand lead and left-hand lead versions of each pattern develops ambidexterity and balance.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="tc-benefit-card">
                    <div class="tc-benefit-icon">🎵</div>
                    <h3>Accent Control</h3>
                    <p>The phrase structure of Three Camps creates natural accent points that help you hear and place musical emphasis within the pattern.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="tc-benefit-card">
                    <div class="tc-benefit-icon">⏱️</div>
                    <h3>Tempo Development</h3>
                    <p>Using a click track while practicing Three Camps builds the internal sense of time that every drummer needs.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="tc-benefit-card">
                    <div class="tc-benefit-icon">🎹</div>
                    <h3>Kit Vocabulary</h3>
                    <p>Once a pattern is comfortable on the snare, moving it around the drumset — toms, cymbals, kick — builds practical fill and solo vocabulary.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- How to Practice -->
    <div class="tc-white">
        <div class="tc-section">
            <div class="tc-label">How to Practice</div>
            <h2>A step-by-step approach to Three Camps</h2>
            <div class="tc-steps">
                <div class="tc-step">
                    <div class="tc-step-num">1</div>
                    <div>
                        <h3>Start slow with a click track</h3>
                        <p>Begin at 60–70 BPM. The goal at slow tempo is accuracy, not speed. Every note should be even and controlled before you increase the tempo.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="tc-step">
                    <div class="tc-step-num">2</div>
                    <div>
                        <h3>Choose one sticking pattern</h3>
                        <p>Select a single sticking pattern from the GK 16ths group. Play it through the entire Three Camps sequence before switching to another pattern.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="tc-step">
                    <div class="tc-step-num">3</div>
                    <div>
                        <h3>Loop a single measure</h3>
                        <p>If a measure feels uneven, isolate it. Click that measure in the app to loop it on its own until it feels natural.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="tc-step">
                    <div class="tc-step-num">4</div>
                    <div>
                        <h3>Play through the full sequence</h3>
                        <p>Once each measure is comfortable, play the full Three Camps sequence from beginning to end without stopping.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="tc-step">
                    <div class="tc-step-num">5</div>
                    <div>
                        <h3>Increase tempo gradually</h3>
                        <p>Move up by 5 BPM only when the pattern feels relaxed and even at the current tempo. Do not rush the progression.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="tc-step">
                    <div class="tc-step-num">6</div>
                    <div>
                        <h3>Move it around the kit</h3>
                        <p>Once a pattern is solid on the snare, apply it to the toms, cymbals, and kick to build orchestration vocabulary.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="tc-bpm-box">
                <h3>Suggested BPM Progression</h3>
                <div class="tc-bpm-row">
                    <span class="tc-bpm-badge">Week 1</span><span>60–70 BPM — Focus on accuracy and even strokes</span>
                </div>
                <div class="tc-bpm-row">
                    <span class="tc-bpm-badge">Week 2</span><span>75–85 BPM — Add the click track and stay relaxed</span>
                </div>
                <div class="tc-bpm-row">
                    <span class="tc-bpm-badge">Week 3</span><span>90–100 BPM — Play through all pattern variations</span>
                </div>
                <div class="tc-bpm-row">
                    <span class="tc-bpm-badge">Week 4+</span><span>Move to the kit — apply patterns around toms and cymbals</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- App CTA -->
    <div class="tc-dark">
        <div class="tc-section" style="text-align:center;">
            <div class="tc-label-light">Try It Now — Free</div>
            <h2 style="color:#fff;">Practice Three Camps in the Interactive App</h2>
