            <button class="tc-btn-primary" style="font-size:1.05rem; padding:16px 40px;" @onclick='() => Nav.NavigateTo("/")'>Launch Three Camps in the Free App →</button>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Common Mistakes -->
    <div class="tc-white">
        <div class="tc-section">
            <div class="tc-label">Common Mistakes</div>
            <h2>What to watch for when practicing Three Camps</h2>
            <div class="tc-mistakes">
                <div class="tc-mistake">
                    <div class="tc-mistake-icon">⚠️</div>
                    <div>
                        <h3>Practicing too fast too soon</h3>
                        <p>Speed before control locks in sloppy technique. Stay at a tempo where every stroke is intentional and even.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="tc-mistake">
                    <div class="tc-mistake-icon">⚠️</div>
                    <div>
                        <h3>Skipping the click track</h3>
                        <p>Practicing without a metronome allows the tempo to drift. The click track is not optional — it is part of the exercise.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="tc-mistake">
                    <div class="tc-mistake-icon">⚠️</div>
                    <div>
                        <h3>Only using one sticking pattern</h3>
                        <p>The power of the Rhythm Library System comes from applying multiple patterns to the same rhythm. Work through the full pattern library.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="tc-mistake">
                    <div class="tc-mistake-icon">⚠️</div>
                    <div>
                        <h3>Not looping difficult measures</h3>
                        <p>If one measure is harder than the rest, isolate it. Looping a single measure until it is solid is more effective than playing through mistakes.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <div class="tc-gray">
        <div class="tc-section">
            <div class="tc-label">FAQ</div>
            <h2>Common questions about Three Camps</h2>
            <div class="tc-faqs">
                <div class="tc-faq">
                    <h3>Is Three Camps suitable for beginners?</h3>
                    <p>Yes. Starting at a slow tempo with simple sticking patterns makes Three Camps accessible from the very beginning. The system scales with your skill level.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="tc-faq">
                    <h3>How long should I practice Three Camps each session?</h3>
                    <p>15 to 20 minutes per session is enough to make consistent progress. Focused, slow practice beats long unfocused sessions every time.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="tc-faq">
                    <h3>Do I need the book to use the app?</h3>
                    <p>No. The free interactive app works on its own as a practice tool. The 83-page PDF book by Gordy Knudtson provides the full system with the complete pattern library.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="tc-faq">
                    <h3>What is the connection to the Syncopation book?</h3>
                    <p>The Rhythm Library System concept is inspired by the practice of applying sticking patterns to the solo pages in Ted Reed's Syncopation. Three Camps is one of the rhythmic frameworks used in this approach.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

